In old records. Full; absolute; perfect; pure. Liege widowhood was pure widow-. hood. Cowell. —Li homage. Homage which, when performed by one sovereign prince to another, included fealty and services, as opposed to simple homage, which was a mere acknowledgment of tenure. (1 BI. Comm. 367; 2 Steph. Comm. 400.) Mozley & Whitley —Liege lord. A sovereign; a superior lord.—Liege poustie. I[n' Scotch law. That state of health which gives. a person full power to dispose of, mortise causa or otherwise, his heritable property. Bell. A deed executed at the time of such a state of health, as opposed to a death-bed conveyance. The term seems to be derived from the Latin

